Class ASTPrintVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • MPC.ASTNullVisitor
      • MPC.ASTPrintVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ASTVisitor, ObjectVisitor, TokenVisitor

    public class ASTPrintVisitor
extends ASTNullVisitor
implements ObjectVisitor, TokenVisitor
    This defines an AST (Abstract Syntax Tree) visitor for printing ASTs.
    Version:
    1.0

    • Field Detail

      • ps

        public final MPCStream ps
        the stream to which to print

      • stack

        private java.util.List<TypeObject> stack
        TypeObjects are inherently recursive (since their methods will normally take a pointer to their TypeObject as an argument). The other possible avenue for our AST to become a directed cyclic graph, via non-object pointers, does not require us to print the recursion, as in that case we merely print the binding.

      • printFullObjectTypes

        private boolean printFullObjectTypes
        normally we want only the name of an object type to print, not the full type (they're big!)
